### Sequential API

The Sequential API is the simplest way to build neural networks. Layers are
stacked in a fixed, linear sequence, making it ideal for straightforward models.

#### Figure 3.4 — Sequential model diagram
<p align='left'><img src='./figure/figure3.4.png' width='60%'></p>

---

### Functional API

The Functional API enables the creation of more flexible architectures with
branching, merging, shared layers, and multi-input or multi-output flows. This
API is used in most real-world deep learning models.

#### Figure 3.5 — Functional API model flow
<p align='left'><img src='./figure/figure3.5.png' width='60%'></p>

---

### Sub-classing API

The Sub-classing API provides maximum control by letting developers define
models using standard Python classes. This is especially useful for research or
custom architectures.

